    "description": "<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >survive As Long As Possible</h2><br>Shoot through hordes of zombies, ankle-biters, and lichs to survive as long as you can. <br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2110930/extras/3eca1268bf683410ed38320a92a2230f.avif?t=1752622151\" width=630 height=232 /></span><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >about This Game</h2><br>This game has a fun aesthetic along with polished mechanics. Every gun is something unique that you most likely haven't seen in other games. They range from the starter weapon, a blowgun to a potato shotgun, even to a reverse gun. Each gun feels unique and has it's pros and cons. The prison/map has different path options giving good replay-ability.<br><br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2110930/extras/3c66ea7e94e6434532589981645edda9.avif?t=1752622151\" width=630 height=80 /></span><br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\">  <li>Do you like old school round-based zombie games?<br>  </li><li>Do you like shooters where you can crouch, walk, run, jump, and slide? Me too, that's why I added them to the game.<br>  </li><li>Do you like cool weapons? I don't have any basic weapons like an AR-15 and wait until you get the wonder weapon!<br>  </li><li>Do you like perks? Same, that's why I added six.<br>  </li><li>Do you like replay-ability? It's about as replayable as any round-based zombie game.</li></ul>",
